General.Name: Scandinavian Biogas Fuels International AB
General.Description: Biokraft International AB, through its subsidiaries, produces and sells biogas in Sweden, South Korea, and Norway. The company engages in recycling local organic waste into renewable energy in the form of biogas and bio-fertilizer using feedstocks, including wastewater sludge, food waste, salmon farming waste, and residues from industrial processes. It offers biogas for use in heat production and electricity generation; liquid biogas that is used as vehicle fuel; and bio-fertilizer. The company was formerly known as Scandinavian Biogas Fuels International AB (publ) and changed its name to Biokraft International AB in June 2023. Biokraft International AB was incorporated in 1995 and is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.
